def gcc(sig, refsig, method="PHAT", interp=1):

    assert method in ["PHAT", "CC"]
    
    n = sig.shape[0] + refsig.shape[0]
    
    SIG = np.fft.rfft(sig, n=n)         
    REFSIG = np.fft.rfft(refsig, n=n)
    R = SIG * np.conj(REFSIG)
    
    if method == "PHAT":
        ccf = np.fft.irfft(R / np.abs(R), n=(interp * n)) # discard the ampltude and keep the phase
    elif method == "CC":
        ccf = np.fft.irfft(R, n=(interp * n))             # standard cross-correlation
    
    max_shift = int(interp * n / 2)

    ccf = np.concatenate((ccf[-max_shift:], ccf[:max_shift+1]))

    shift = np.argmax(np.abs(ccf)) - max_shift
    return shift, ccf, max_shift

def gcc_phat(sig, refsig):
    return gcc(sig, refsig, method="PHAT")

def get_topK(top_k, arr):
    top_k_idx=arr.argsort()[::-1][0:top_k]
    return top_k_idx

1. Read Audios¶

  • We play two sources, 0 and 1, simoutineously.
  • To obtain the TOAs of LOS and ECHO of each source, we insert pseudo-random white noise immediately proceeding each source.

import IPython

interp=1 

fs = 48000
frame = np.load('./frame.npy')

subframes = []
for i in range(4):   #  4 audio channels
    subframes.append(frame[i::8])


print("Click to play the audio: (To change the channel, switch the index (0, 1, 2, 3) of subframes):")
IPython.display.Audio(subframes[0], rate=fs)

2. For each audio channel, we extract the ToAs of LOS and ECHO of source 0 from it.¶

In [4]:
%matplotlib inline

fs = 48000
np.random.seed(0)
awgn0 = np.random.randn(int(0.1*fs))  # PN noise played by source 0 




s0_los_idxs = []  # LOS index of source 0
s0_echo_idxs = [] # ECHO index of source 0




for i in range(4):
    
    # convolve channel i with the awgn0 to detect LOS and ECHO
    cor = signal.fftconvolve(subframes[i], awgn0[::-1])
    cor = abs(cor)
    cor = cor / np.max(cor)

    
    # find LOS and ECHO indexs
    peak_idxs, _ = signal.find_peaks(cor, height=np.max(cor)*0.55, distance=15) 
    
    
    
    #plot LOS and ECHO paths.
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    plt.plot(cor, color="#4d4d4d")
    plt.plot(peak_idxs[0], cor[peak_idxs[0]], "o", color="red", ms=10, label="LOS of Source 0")
    plt.plot(peak_idxs[1], cor[peak_idxs[1]], "x", color="red", ms=10, label="ECHO of Source 0")
    
    plt.title("Mic. " + str(i), fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.xlim([peak_idxs[0]-100, peak_idxs[0]+ 3000])
    plt.xlabel("Index [sample]", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.xticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.ylabel("CIR", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.yticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.legend(fontsize=fontsize)
    
    
    #save the ground truth
    s0_los_idxs.append(peak_idxs[0])
    s0_echo_idxs.append(peak_idxs[1])
    
    
    #remove awgn0 from the audio,  since awgn0 is not supposed to exist in practice
    subframes[i][peak_idxs[0] -int(0.1*fs):peak_idxs[0]+int(0.3*fs)] = 0

    cor = abs(cor)
    cor = cor / np.max(cor)
        
    # find LOS and ECHO indexs

4. Next, we calculate and plot CCFs between different microphone pairs, along with the ground truth.¶

In [6]:
cc_peaks = []
cc_peaks_height = []

s0_los_shifts = []
s0_echo_shifts = []

s1_los_shifts = []
s1_echo_shifts = []


plt.figure(figsize=(15,12))


for (i, j) in [(0, 1), (0, 2), (0,3)]: # For microphone pairs <0,1>, <0, 2>, and <0, 3>

    #use gcc_phat to calculate CCF between signals from microphone pairs <i,j>
    shift, cc, max_shift = gcc_phat(subframes[i], subframes[j]) 
    cc = abs(cc)
    cc= cc / np.max(cc)

    peak_idxs, _ = signal.find_peaks(cc,  height=np.max(cc)*0.1)

#     if(j - i == 1):
#         top_k_idx = get_topK(6, cc)  
#         for idx in top_k_idx:
#             if idx not in peak_idxs:
#                 peak_idxs = np.concatenate([peak_idxs, [idx]])

    cc_peaks.append(np.array(peak_idxs) - max_shift)
    cc_peaks_height.append(cc[peak_idxs])

    plt.figure(figsize=(10,3))
    plt.plot(np.arange(len(cc)) - max_shift, cc, '-')

    plt.plot(np.array(peak_idxs) - max_shift, cc[peak_idxs], '^', color='orange')
    plt.xlim([-50*interp, 50*interp])

    
    print("For Microphone pair:", i, j, ":")
    
    #calulcate and plot TDoAs of LOS and ECHO of source 0
    s0_los_shift = -(s0_los_idxs[j] - s0_los_idxs[i])
    s0_echo_shift = -(s0_echo_idxs[j] - s0_echo_idxs[i])
    print("\t source 0,  TDoA of LOS:", s0_los_shift, "[sample]")
    print("\t source 0,  TDoA of ECHO:", s0_echo_shift, "[sample]")
    
    plt.plot([s0_los_shift*interp], [cc[s0_los_shift+max_shift]], 'o', color='red', ms=10, label="LOS Source 0")
    plt.plot([s0_echo_shift*interp], [cc[s0_echo_shift+max_shift]], 'x', color='red', ms=10,label="ECHO Source 0")


    
    #calulcate and plot TDoAs of LOS and ECHO of source 1
    s1_los_shift = -(s1_los_idxs[j] - s1_los_idxs[i])
    s1_echo_shift = -(s1_echo_idxs[j] - s1_echo_idxs[i])
    print("\t source 1, TDoA of LOS:", s1_los_shift, "[sample]")
    print("\t source 1, TDoA of ECHO:", s1_echo_shift, "[sample]")
    
    
    plt.plot([s1_los_shift*interp], [cc[s1_los_shift+max_shift]], 'o', color='blue', ms=10, label="LOS Source 1")
    plt.plot([s1_echo_shift*interp], [cc[s1_echo_shift+max_shift]], 'x', color='blue',ms=10, label="ECHO Source 1")

    
    
    
    plt.title("Microphone Pair: " + str(i) + ", " + str(j), fontsize=fontsize)
   
    plt.xlabel("Time shift [sample]", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.xticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.ylabel("Cor.", fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.yticks( fontsize=fontsize)
    plt.legend(fontsize=15, loc="upper right")
    
    
    
    s0_los_shifts.append(s0_los_shift)
    s0_echo_shifts.append(s0_echo_shift)
    s1_los_shifts.append(s1_los_shift)
    s1_echo_shifts.append(s1_echo_shift)
